{"overview":"This E minor nocturne unfolds in a clear ternary-like five-section arch, characterized by a pervasive tension between minor and major modes—most strikingly in the modal mixture shift to B major (bar 18) and the coda's oscillation between E major and E minor tonics. The piece's most distinctive harmonic fingerprint is its relentless deployment of diminished seventh chords as chromatic intensifiers throughout all sections, paired with an arpeggiated bass texture that anchors the nocturne idiom while the upper voice traces increasingly ornate melodic lines.","cross_piece_tags":["nocturne","ternary","modal_mixture","arpeggiated_bass","lyrical","melancholic","chromatic_mediant","meditative"]}
